This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a novel weakly-supervised semantic segmentation algorithm based on Deep Convolutional Neural Network (DCNN) for image analysis. It also mentions the PASCAL VOC 2012 dataset, which is a popular benchmark dataset for computer vision tasks. 

It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it uses a DCNN for learning and making predictions. 

The Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper proposes a method for learning transferrable knowledge, which is a common goal in AI research. 

The Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of an attention model, which is a technique commonly used in natural language processing. 

Finally, the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper deals with image analysis, which is a common multimedia task.
